(thirdQuint)Ondansetron for Bipolar Disorder and Alcohol Use Disorders.

 A total of 70 outpatients with alcohol use disorder and BPD, cyclothymic disorder, schizoaffective disorder (bipolar type), or MDD with mixed features will be enrolled in a 12-week, randomized, double-blind, parallel-group, placebo-controlled study of ondansetron.

 Participant will receive either ondansetron or a placebo for 12 weeks.

 He or she has an equal chance of receiving ondansetron or placebo.

 Randomization will be stratified based on > 4 or 4 drinking days per week at start of the study.

 Ondansetron or placebo will be given at 0.

5 milligrams twice a day for the first 4 weeks.

